v 3
d catllm: LLM-powered classification and extraction for text data
d
d catllm provides a Stata interface to the cat-stack ecosystem of Python
d packages for automating the categorization of text data using large
d language models (LLMs). Supports text classification, category discovery,
d saturation analysis, and text summarization. Domain-specific prompts
d (political, sentiment, academic, survey, cognitive, web) are available
d via the domain() option. Works with 8+ LLM providers (OpenAI, Anthropic,
d Google, and more).
d
d Requires: Stata 16+ with Python integration, Python 3.8+, cat-stack >= 1.2.0
d
d Author: Christopher Soria
d Support: chrissoria@berkeley.edu
d
d Distribution-Date: 20260517

